Then, using the tangent addition formula: \[ T_{n+1} = \frac{T_n + \tan x}{1 - T_n \tan x} \] If we write \( T_n = \frac{P_n}{Q_n} \), then: \[ \frac{P_{n+1}}{Q_{n+1}} = \frac{\frac{P_n}{Q_n} + \tan x}{1 - \frac{P_n}{Q_n} \tan x} = \frac{P_n + Q_n \tan x}{Q_n - P_n \tan x} \] Therefore, \( P_{n+1} = P_n + Q_n \tan x \) and \( Q_{n+1} = Q_n - P_n \tan x \). But since \( \tan x \) is a variable here, this recursion might not be helpful unless we treat \( \tan x \) as a variable and equate coefficients. Alternatively, note that if we let \( t = \tan x \), then \( T_n = \tan(nx) \) can be expressed as a rational function in \( t \). The recursion above gives: \[ T_{n+1} = \frac{T_n + t}{1 - T_n t} \] Expressed as a continued fraction, this recursion can be used to build up \( T_{n+1} \) from \( T_n \). Starting from \( T_1 = t \), we can generate \( T_2 = \frac{t}{1 - t^2}
